f our ecological predicament. Seeking to comprehend both the multifaceted complexity of contemporary environmental problems and the zeitgeist as it unfolds, Freyfogle explores such diverse topics as morality, the nature of reality (and the reality of nature), animal welfare, social justice movements, and market politics. The result is a learned and inspiring rallying cry to achieve balance, a call to use our knowledge to more accurately identify the dividing line between living in and on the world and destruction. “To use nature,” Freyfogle writes, “but not to abuse it.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHuman beingsxEffect of environment onzUnited States. 0aHuman beingsxEffect of environment on. 0aNature and civilizationzUnited States. 0aNature and civilization. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aconservation.  acultural reform.  aenvironmental philosophy.  aenvironmental studies.  aepistemology.  aliberal individualism.  ametaphysics.  anew economy.  asources of normativity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107119360 cprintz978022632639940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226326429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226326429/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles